     <p>
          <xr pageref="N" ref="ME.IS.093021082020">Montenegro</xr>
    , formerly part of the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia (FRY), and subsequently part of the State Union of Serbia and Montenegro, lies in south-eastern Europe. The FRY was established in 1992, following the disintegration of the Socialist Federal People’s Republic of Yugoslavia. The State Union of Serbia and Montenegro was formally established with the adoption of a Constitutional Charter in February 2003. On 21 May 2006 a referendum was conducted in Montenegro, at which some 55.5% of votes were cast in favour of independence. On 3 June Montenegro’s legislature formally endorsed independence. Podgorica is the capital. The principal language is Montenegrin.
  </p>
